Let's think step by step. Let us first write down what the problem statement tells us about $P$:

\begin{align*}
x^2-2x+2&\le P(x)\le 2x^2-4x+3,\\
P(11)&=181.
\end{align*}

In particular, note that $f(11)=121-22+2=101<181$. Hence, since $f(11)<P(11)$, we know that

$$f(x)=x^2-2x+2<Q(x).$$Similarly, $g(11)=242-44+3=201>181,$ so $g(11)>P(11),$ and hence $$Q(x)<g(x)=2x^2-4x+3.$$Combining these facts, we obtain \begin{align*}
f(x)&\le Q(x)\le g(x),\\
x^2-2x+2 &\le Q(x)\le2x^2-4x+3,
\end{align*}where equality holds in the left inequality when $x$ is a root of the equation $x^2-2x+2=P(x)$
